{"type": "qna", "messages": [{"id": "850932090806730755", "type": 0, "content": "Bourbon, how accessible do you expect fishing to be in the game? Stardew's fishing is either loved or hated, do you expect Palia's to be the same? (Stardew eventually had to add a training rod in for the people that just couldn't fish at all)", "channel_id": "829113775876735026", "author": {"id": "166474685201121280", "username": "Roan", "avatar": "77659452c410b42c39925638f310e859", "discriminator": "9961", "public_flags": 0}, "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "mentions": [], "mention_roles": [], "pinned": false, "mention_everyone": false, "tts": false, "timestamp": "2021-06-06T03:00:20.002000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2021-06-06T03:00:51.294000+00:00", "flags": 0, "components": []}, {"id": "850933001214492681", "type": 19, "content": "That's a great question!  I'm aware of Stardew's infamous fishing difficulty.  We are aiming for a similar level of depth but with a gentler difficulty curve.  You should be able to succeed at low-level fishing even if you are not good at the mechanic.", "channel_id": "829113775876735026", "author": {"id": "839344781385138198", "username": "Bourbon", "avatar": "e886175eaaf3f05f644a3088f36589cb", "discriminator": "2251", "public_flags": 0}, "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "mentions": [{"id": "166474685201121280", "username": "Roan", "avatar": "77659452c410b42c39925638f310e859", "discriminator": "9961", "public_flags": 0}], "mention_roles": [], "pinned": false, "mention_everyone": false, "tts": false, "timestamp": "2021-06-06T03:03:57.060000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "flags": 0, "components": [], "message_reference": {"channel_id": "829113775876735026", "guild_id": "809856101326913567", "message_id": "850932090806730755"}, "hit": true}]}